ma (subtle) body to\nother bodies at the expiry of good actions which contribute to the enjoyment\nof material pleasures ( _vide_ Apte\'s Dictionary).\n\n[267:1](tmu32.htm#fr_265) Melana is lit., joining. This is the key to this\nscience which seems to be kept profoundly secret and revealed by adepts only\nat initiation, as will appear from the subsequent passages in this Upanisha\xe1\xb8\x8d.\n\n[268:1](tmu32.htm#fr_267) All these are very mystic.\n\n[269:1](tmu32.htm#fr_268) Probably it here means some part below the skull.\n\n[269:2](tmu32.htm#fr_269) Certain motions of the fingers and hands in the\npronunciation of man\xe1\xb9\xadras.\n\n[271:1](tmu32.htm#fr_270) V\xc4\x81k is of four kinds (as said here) par\xc4\x81, pasyan\xe1\xb9\xad\xc4\xab,\nma\xe1\xb8\x8dhyam\xc4\x81, and vaikhar\xc4\xab. Vaikhar\xc4\xab being the lowest and the grossest of sounds,\nand part being the highest. In evolution v\xc4\x81k begins from the highest to the\nlowest and in involution it takes a reverse order, to merge into the highest\nsubtle sound (Par\xc4\x81).\n\n[271:2](tmu32.htm#fr_271) The first three aspects of consciousness refer to\nthe gross, subtle, and k\xc4\x81ra\xe1\xb9\x87a bodies of men, while the second three aspects\nrefer to the three bodies of the universe. This is from the standpoint of the\nthree bodies.\n\n[271:3](tmu32.htm#fr_272) The egg of man--this shows that man in his formation\nis and appears as an egg, just as the universe is, and appears as an egg.\n\n[272:1](tmu32.htm#fr_273) It is the consciousness that becomes distorted and\nis unable to cognise itself through the bodies.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: Index of Proper Names](tmu33.htm)\n\n'